{
  "text": "To test whether the low nucleotide diversity observed in Tanuki haplogroup is also translated into extended homozygosity, a hallmark of a selective sweep, we simulated expected Runs of Homozygosity (ROH) assuming demographic parameters outlined in [CITATION_1] ) and different recombination rates (see methods for details). We found that the ROH values observed for the Tanuki single nucleotide variants in the 1KGP East Asian populations is significantly higher than what is expected under neutrality based on frequency matched simulation results with r = 200, the most realistic parameter from the observation ( Figure 5C , P , 2.5x10 212 , Wilcoxon-Rank-Sum Test). The averaged ROH of the Tanuki haplogroup was 16Kb.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2190655"
